Get feature-level data to be used in the MSstatsSummarizationOutput function

getProcessed.Rd

Get feature-level data to be used in the MSstatsSummarizationOutput function

getProcessed(input)

Arguments

input

data.table processed by dataProcess subfunctions

Value

data.table processed by dataProcess subfunctions

Examples

raw = DDARawData
method = "TMP"
cens = "NA"
impute = TRUE
MSstatsConvert::MSstatsLogsSettings(FALSE)
input = MSstatsPrepareForDataProcess(raw, 2, NULL)
#> INFO  [2021-05-14 23:04:09] ** Features with one or two measurements across runs are removed.
#> INFO  [2021-05-14 23:04:09] ** Fractionation handled.
#> INFO  [2021-05-14 23:04:09] ** Updated quantification data to make balanced design. Missing values are marked by NA
input = MSstatsNormalize(input, "EQUALIZEMEDIANS")
input = MSstatsMergeFractions(input)
input = MSstatsHandleMissing(input, "TMP", TRUE, "NA", 0.999)
#> INFO  [2021-05-14 23:04:09] ** Log2 intensities under cutoff = 13.456  were considered as censored missing values.
#> INFO  [2021-05-14 23:04:09] ** Log2 intensities = NA were considered as censored missing values.
input_all = MSstatsSelectFeatures(input, "all") # all features
#> INFO  [2021-05-14 23:04:09] ** Use all features that the dataset originally has.
input_5 = MSstatsSelectFeatures(data.table::copy(input),
"topN", top_n = 5) # top 5 features
#> INFO  [2021-05-14 23:04:09] ** Use top5 features that have highest average of log2(intensity) across runs.

proc1 = getProcessed(input_all)
proc2 = getProcessed(input_5)

proc1
